{"cursor":"5590","size":14,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox Union |name= TUCA - CSA |country= The Americas |affiliation= ITUC\n|members= 50 million in 29 countries |full_name= TUCA Trade Union Confederation\nof the Americas |native_name= ConfederaciÃ³n Sindical de los Trabajadores y\nTrabajadoras de las Americas |image= |founded= 2008 (1951) |current= |head=\n|dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= Sao Paulo, Brazil\n|people= Victor BÃ¡ez Mosqueira, General Secretary; Linda Chavez Thompson,\nPresident |website= [http://www.csa-csi.org/ www.csa-csi.org/] |footnotes= }}\n\n\n\n\nThe 'TUCA Trade Union Confederation of the Americas (TUCA-CSA)' is the regional\norganization of the International Trade Union Confederation (ITUC) for the\nAmericas. It was formed in March 2008 to succeed the ICFTU Inter American\nRegional Organisation of Workers (CIOSL/ORIT), after ICFTU merged to ITUC. The\norganisation has 65 affiliated or fraternal organisations, in 29 countries,\nrepresenting 50 million workers.\n\nThe COISL/ORIT was formed in 1951, and describes its objective as being to work\nfor independent, autonomous, democratic unions throughout the Americas.","linknr":223,"url":"ITUC_Regional_Organisation_for_the_Americas","recorded":1375090199,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Trade_Union_Confederation_of_the_Americas&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Trade_Union_Confederation_of_the_Americas&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Trade_Union_Confederation_of_the_Americas","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//b